quality (defect detection). Stubbed responses would always pass and miss real model failures/non-determinism. Rejected Workflow because the behavior asks for a single outcome (detect a real defect), not correctness of multiple sequential model decisions.","test_description":"Run the real model on a PR diff with a seeded known bug and assert at least one returned finding correctly targets that defect class/location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.14}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module state consistency (posted-comment results -> summary assembler). It needs wiring validation across components, but not real OS/network/model output quality. Rejected System because real API is not required to reproduce ID-correlation bugs; rejected Agentic/Workflow because model content quality is not the assertion.","test_description":"Execute posting-result collection and summary-generation together with run-scoped IDs; assert each summary item references an existing inline-comment ID created in that same run context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is loss during pipeline handoff/aggregation (inline findings -> summary payload), which is beyond a single function but reproducible in-process. Rejected System because no real network/OS behavior is required to trigger drop bugs; rejected Agentic/Workflow because this checks transport/completeness, not model decision quality.","test_description":"Run the aggregation/serialization path with multiple inline findings (including edge cases) and assert payload cardinality/content preserves all findings before post call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real pull request and real end-to-end API interactions. Mocking HTTP/platform behavior can hide auth, ordering, payload, and API contract failures. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because findings are fixed precomputed (no model-quality dependency).","test_description":"Run the pipeline against a real test PR using a fixed findings fixture; verify diff read succeeds, inline comments are created, and top-level summary posts successfully in order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.89,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline combining real model-generated analysis with downstream posting stages. It requires sequential correctness across agentic and non-agentic steps; single-step Agentic is insufficient to catch handoff/orchestration failures across the whole run.","test_description":"Execute an unattended end-to-end run on a real PR using the live model; assert analysis produces findings, inline comments are posted, and summary is posted with consistent linkage and completion status.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integ